            <span class="utterance" who="#heislerA" start="2094.760" end="x">And that was our luck. [The following note was inserted in the first-draft translation by Mr. Bernard Wolf who himself was in <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a> at that time: He is probably referring here to the death march from <a class="placename" href="#vothC84" type="camp">Ohrdurf</a> to <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a>. 'Twelve thousand prisoners left <a class="placename" href="#vothC84" type="camp">Ohrdurf</a>, less than half arrived in <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a>.'] From there we came to <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a>, and we were pushed into.... We believed that.... In <a class="placename" href="#vothC15" type="camp">Buchenwald</a> we were put near the crematory, so we believed that we were being taken to the crematory, but luckily...</span>
