            <span class="utterance" who="#heislerA" start="2283.736" end="x">Nothing. We only saw them leaving the watchtowers. It was so. Afterwards we dis-...dis-...discovered...heard that from <a class="placename" href="#vothL42">Weimar</a> the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> commander had telephoned to demolish the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, [he telephoned] one hour after the liberation. He did not know yet that the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> had already been liberated. It was at half past four. So the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> elder -- he was a prisoner -- answered him, 'Yes, yes, we will demolish their heads.' If we had not been liberated an hour before, they would have demolished the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
